I found the source of the problem. It is located here in VDatePicker.tsx line 232 where allowedMonths function is executed.
Here line  234 looks like this:
```js
const startOfMonth = adapter.parseISO(`${year.value}-${month + 1}-01`)
```
Given month is from January (index 0) to September (index 8) "month + 1" resolves to single digit and startOfMonth date resolves to e.g. 2025-1-01, which results in "Invalid date" and month gets disabled.
I found a utility used in framework "padStart", which can be used like this:
```js
const month = padStart(String(date.getMonth() + 1), 2, '0');
```
This would result in a month with 2 digits always (e.g. January would be 01).
With the fix it could look like this:
```js
if (typeof props.allowedDates === 'function') {
        const formattedMonth = padStart(String(month + 1), 2, '0');
        const startOfMonth = adapter.parseISO(`${year.value}-${formattedMonth}-01`);
        return isAllowedInRange(startOfMonth, adapter.endOfMonth(startOfMonth));
}
```
If it's ok I can make a PR.

