@djsmith85 @frq-asgard-josi

I did some digging, and here's my theory.

[proxy-agent](https://github.com/TooTallNate/proxy-agents/blob/main/packages/proxy-agent) depends on [proxy-from-env](https://github.com/Rob--W/proxy-from-env) to process proxy-related environment variables.

The [logic](https://github.com/Rob--W/proxy-from-env/blob/master/index.js#L64) in `proxy-from-env` for interpreting `NO_PROXY` may be the root cause.

```js
function shouldProxy(hostname, port) {
  var NO_PROXY =
    (getEnv('npm_config_no_proxy') || getEnv('no_proxy')).toLowerCase();
  if (!NO_PROXY) {
    return true;  // Always proxy if NO_PROXY is not set.
  }
  if (NO_PROXY === '*') {
    return false;  // Never proxy if wildcard is set.
  }
}
function getEnv(key) {
  return process.env[key.toLowerCase()] || process.env[key.toUpperCase()] || '';
}
```

`npm_config_no_proxy` has higher priority, and if set, `no_proxy` or `NO_PROXY` won't be effective. This [issue](https://github.com/Rob--W/proxy-from-env/issues/13) and [fix](https://github.com/Rob--W/proxy-from-env/pull/27) are still open.

